Etymology[edit]

Related to pēs (“foot”).

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ekˈspe.di.oː/, [ɛkˈspɛ.d̪i.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ekˈspe.di.o/, [ɛkˈspɛː.d̪i.ɔ]

Verb[edit]

expediō (present infinitive expedīre, perfect active expedīvī or expediī, supine expedītum); fourth conjugation

  1. I bring forward, I dispatch, I expedite.
  2. I procure or obtain
  3. I am profitable, serviceable, advantageous, expedient.

Descendants[edit]

  • Vulgar Latin: *expedītāre
    • Albanian: shpëtoj
  • English: expedite
  • Esperanto: ekspedi
  • French: expédier
  • Galician: espir
  • Ido: expediar
  • Italian: spedire
  • Portuguese: expedir, despir
  • Spanish: expedir
  • Venetian: spedir
